# STEP 0a (tailscaled cold-start kill): the 2026-07-02 22:30 field boot showed a cold
# tailscaled needing >5s to bind its socket; the old lib killed it at 5s, four times over.
# A slow starter must be WAITED OUT (with progress logging) and then come Up normally.
desc tailscale-lib: slow daemon start survives the socket wait and comes Up (no kill)
invoke tslib
tsdaemon slow:80
sdfile+ .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.state
tsdrv up
expect_exit 0
expect_trace TSDRV up rc=0
expect_file_has .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.log	still waiting for tailscaled socket
expect_file_has .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.log	tier-1 up: reusing persisted login
expect_trace_absent KILLALL tailscaled
